*** Bug 77895 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
*** Bug 77905 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

You might want to try the workspace rebuilder plug-in (URLs may be split): 

http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/index.cgi/%7Echeckout%7E/platform-core-home/downloads/tools/readme_restorer_1.0.0.html

The download can be done from here:

http://dev.eclipse.org/viewcvs/index.cgi/%7Echeckout%7E/platform-core-home/downloads.html

Another thing: your project contents is not at risk. If you have just a couple
of projects and have no important metadata to worry about (preferences, manually
created tasks, resource properties, things like that), instead of using the
workspace rebuilder, rename the .metadata dir inside the workspace manually,
start Eclipse, and create the projects again using exactly the same locations.
The existing contents will be discovered.

If you could attach your problematic .metadata dir as a ZIP file to this PR so
we can investigate the problem, that would be good.
Please reopen when you can provide the information requested above.
